{{zh-hanzi|[[工]][[欲]][[善]][[其]][[事]]，[[必]][[先]][[利]][[其]][[器]]}}
==Mandarin==
===Etymology===
Literally: If a workman wishes to do a good job, he must first sharpen his tools.
*{{RQ:Confucius}}

===Proverb===
{{cmn-proverb|ts|pin=gōng yù shàn qí shì, bì xiān lì qí qì|pint=gong1yu4shan4qi2shi4bi4xian1li4qi2qi4|rs=工00}}

# One must have good tools in order to do a good job.